snippet.textDisplay:
I grew up on this method:
Credit to my mom!

Prep:
1.32 oz or whatever plastic cup ( don’t plan on drinking out of it)
2. Mild Soap( or your favorite body wash)
3. Combine with water ( lukewarm water- avoid ice cold water if can)

Combine and mix the soap and water in cup( you can also prep this in your bathtub just remember to keep a separate empty medium size cup or whatever size u use).
Second is to flush first after your done your business or whatever of number 1 or both.
Third is to Manually bidet style this. It may be awkward at first but basically using your free hand to wash yourself down there cleanly. You can add more water from the tub if needed more rinsing whatever residue( including soap) until no more needed.

It does work... its like same thing showering or having a electric bidet wash and bathe yourself there but using a cup and body wash. Be gentle with yourself sense.

This is what my mom grew up in the province when toilet paper is luxury back in her time.

And Always WASH YOUR HANDS AFTERWARDS. No exceptions.

This is basically if last but not least if ran out of toilet paper.. or receipt paper or whatever on hand...

Paper towels are useful to use to wipe down there just keep in mind and anyone to be aware in the household that after wiping yourself using the paper towel is to throw it in the trash and not dispose in the 🚽 itself. Newspapers help too! These are another alternative.

Hope this may help.
